## Opposed-Trace / Defense-Matrix Section

Opposed-Trace Harness:
- Actor separation: <<actor_separation|attacker = <addr>; defender = <addr>; harness drives both as independent keypairs|enumerate every actor (attacker, victim, defender, observer) with a distinct keypair / role-binding so a triager cannot collapse them into the same identity>>
- Attacker move: <<attacker_move|<attacker action>|the unmodified protocol-owned call the attacker invokes (function name + file:line)>>
- Defender's best contestation: <<defender_best_contest|<defender action>|the unmodified protocol-owned call the defender CAN make to block the attacker outcome - cite file:line. If no in-protocol contestation exists, state "no defender move available" and cite the source>>
- Defender outcome under PoC: <<defender_outcome|<reverts | no-op | succeeds-but-impact-stands>|did the defender's contestation succeed? If yes, the attack is structurally blocked - walk back severity>>
- Attacker outcome under defended condition: <<attacker_outcome_defended|<impact still lands | impact blocked>|state explicitly whether the attacker impact survives once the defender takes their best move>>
- Negative control: <<negative_control|<patched code / canonical upstream proves contest succeeds>|cite the patched-code / canonical-upstream run that shows the defense WORKS in the fixed/clean path - confirms the bug is the attribution-gap not a harness artifact>>
- Race / ordering analysis: <<race_ordering|<who runs first matters because <reason>>|describe how the harness orders attacker/defender moves and whether reordering changes the outcome>>
- Verdict: <<r44_verdict|attacker-impact-survives-best-defense|attacker-impact-survives-best-defense | defender-contests-successfully (walk back) | race-dependent (state cap)>>

